        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <p><b>Context:</b> considering the objectives set in Vision and Scope and user requirements from Software Requirements Specification, it was considered to proceed with the enlisted below functionalities for the realization of the informational support within the mobile banking application.</p>

<p><b>Requirements</b>:</p>

<p>Requirement 1: Proceed money transfers between the user's accounts.</p>

<p>Requirement 2: Make transfers to Raiffeisen accounts.</p>

<p>Requirement 3: Make transfers to Raiffeisen cards.</p>

<p>Requirement 4: Transfer funds to accounts of other banks.</p>

<p>Requirement 5: Transfer funds to cards of other banks.</p>

<p><del><b>Functionality</b>: A user shall be able to use the mobile banking application with the functionality of the "bank in the phone", namely to be able to transfer funds between owned accounts and cards as well as to send the funds to third-party accounts and cards using the application installed in the smartphone and being authorized for such transactions.</del> <font color="#FF0000">(considering the tutor's comment)</font></p>

<p><b>Details</b>: The operations shall be possible to arrange and perform within the application, with no third-party involvement, except the verification/validation mechanisms for the transfers or payments completion via the respective module of the application.</p>

<p>The options shall include:</p>
<ul>
	<li>account-to-account transfers (rules - TBD),</li>
	<li>account-to-card transfers (rules - TBD).</li>
	<li>card-to-card transfers (rules - TBD),</li>
	<li>additional combinations and options (TBD).</li>
	<li>visualization of additional commission (in case there will be...)</li>
	<li>ability to store receipt after the transfer/transaction is made or denied.</li>
</ul>


<p><b>Decisions</b>: the idea has been supported by the Program Board at the Program Review meeting on 13 June 2021, the decision adopted is reflected with the Vision and Scope and SRS documents.</p>

<p>Commission for the transfers shall be calculated in the respective RBA Commission Framework from DD-MM-YYYY.</p>

<p><b>Requirements are based on:</b> SRS at <b><a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Q4D-p8agUYv62VAKTQxKVwP4drKb9MDEFH1jw_Cs8d4/edit?usp=sharing" class="external-link" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Q4D-p8agUYv62VAKTQxKVwP4drKb9MDEFH1jw_Cs8d4/edit?usp=sharing</a></b></p>
